# Commit Message Attribution Rule

Do not include any AI/tool attribution in git commit messages.

## Never include phrases like

- "created by Cursor"
- "generated by Cursor"
- "co-authored-by Cursor"
- "AI-generated"
- any wording that attributes authorship to tools instead of the developer/team

## Required commit message style

- Focus on user-facing or engineering intent (why the change exists)
- Keep messages concise and repository-style consistent
- Use neutral engineering language without tool branding

## Examples

- Bad: `feat: add cart quantity guards (created by Cursor)`
- Good: `feat: enforce quantity guardrails for cart and PDP flows`
